<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
Based on the descriptions and related iconographies, all of these species share the set of discriminant features that characterise the new section and distinguish it very well from all the known sections of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Alliaceae" genus="Allium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Allium">Allium</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5642/aliso.20062201.31" author="Friesen, N" journalOrPublisher="Aliso" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="372 - 395" refId="B34" refString="Friesen, N, Fritsch, RM, Blattner, FR, 2006. Phylogeny and new intrageneric classification of Allium L. (Alliaceae) based on nuclear rDNA ITS sequences. Aliso 22 (1): 372 - 395, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5642/aliso.20062201.31" title="Phylogeny and new intrageneric classification of Allium L. (Alliaceae) based on nuclear rDNA ITS sequences." url="https://doi.org/10.5642/aliso.20062201.31" volume="22" year="2006">Friesen et al. 2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Khassanov, FO" journalOrPublisher="Stapfia" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="171 - 174" refId="B43" refString="Khassanov, FO, Shomuradov, HF, Kadyrov, GU, 2011. Taxonomic revision of Allium L. sect. Allium s. l. in Central Asia. Stapfia 95: 171 - 174" title="Taxonomic revision of Allium L. sect. Allium s. l. in Central Asia." volume="95" year="2011">Khassanov et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
